# Human review is the HITL gate. With branch protection set to
# "Require review from Code Owners":
#
#   - PRs touching units/ (new or edited knowledge) require reviewer approval.
#   - PRs touching only events/ have no code owner, so they need no human
#     review — validation CI + the auto-merge-events workflow handle them.
#     That asymmetry is deliberate: cheap to confirm, expensive to introduce.
#
# Replace the placeholder teams before enabling branch protection.

/units/       @YOUR-ORG/knowledge-reviewers
/assistants/  @YOUR-ORG/knowledge-reviewers
/.cq/         @YOUR-ORG/knowledge-admins
/.github/     @YOUR-ORG/knowledge-admins
/scripts/     @YOUR-ORG/knowledge-admins
